    <text id="R1421101T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union Chief of Staff Henry Halleck writes Colonel Bowrs with information on
                    December, 1864, Confederate troop positions. Halleck reports that Confederate
                    General Jubal Early remains stationed in Staunton, VA.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    WAR DEPARTMENT
                    <name type="recipient">Lieut. Col. T. S. BOWRS,<lb/> Assistant Adjutant-Gen.,
                        City Point, Va.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-12-30">December 30, 1864.</date>
                        <name type="place">Washington,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Our scouts visited the old man last night, and returned this morning with report
                    that re-enforcements (supposed to be part of one division and a brigade from
                    another) were sent from Richmond to Hood on Wednesday last. Early remains at
                    Staunton, with no change in his numbers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>H. W. HALLECK,<lb/> Maj.-Gen. and Chief of Staff.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
